                                              
                Web Application - Prime Number Validator

Description:
- This web application is designed to check whether a number is prime or not.
- The user needs to enter the number in the text box and click "Submit". Result is displayed on the webpage - whether the number entered is prime or not.

Webpage URL: ec2-52-11-10-109.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com:5000

Directory structure of my project is as below:
/prime.py
/usr/share/tomcat7/webapps/assign1/prime.jsp
/usr/share/tomcat7/webapps/assign1/prime2.jsp

The web application uses Tomcat7 to execute. Below are the steps to setup and start tomcat7 on Amazon AMI:
1. sudo yum install tomcat7 tomcat7-webapps tomcat7-admin-webapps tomcat-docs (install tomcat7)
2. sudo -i
3. cd /usr/share/tomcat7
4. cd conf
5. sudo chmod 777 /usr/share/tomcat7/conf/tomcat-users.xml (Gives permission to edit xml file)
6. Change username and password in tomcat-users.xml file to use Manager-GUI
7. sudo chmod 777 /usr/share/tomcat7/webapps (Gives permission to create folders in webapps)
8. Create a folder for your project in webapps and save your project files there.
9. sudo service tomcat7 start (To start tomcat server)




